						               													<description>This Hard &amp;amp; Calcined Earth&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Set in North Africa during 1940-43 the game is a campaign level card game.  &amp;#10;It portrays the broad sweep of events and strategic issues surrounding the famous desert battles in a game that is different each time it is played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The name is a quotation taken from the beginning of episode 8 of the famous 1973 Thames TV series &amp;quot;The World At War&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game deals with all the complexities of the historical campaign yet is physically small enough to put it in your pocket and play it down the pub, on a train, or in the garden. &amp;#10;The rules are simple to learn but difficult to master.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With THACE events affect the outcome of the game but you always have some element of control.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game provides an alternative, feasible history of the North Africa Campaign every time it's played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is, in other words, a campaign in your pocket.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Rules &amp;amp; Historical Chronology including both colour &amp;amp; monochrome covers.&amp;#10;     Designer's notes.&amp;#10;     Set of colour cards. A4 version (8 pages with 11 terrain, 20 strategic &amp;amp; 21 operational cards).&amp;#10;     Set of colour cards. US letter version (10 pages with cards as above).&amp;#10;     Instructions for cutting out the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
